   <text>
      <body>
         <div type="letter">
            <pb n="1" facs="Edgeworth_Huntington_XXXX_1817_05_02_page01.jpg"/>
            <opener>
               <dateline>
                  <date when="1817-05-02"/>May 2<hi rend="superscript">d</hi> 1817<lb/>
                  <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Edgeworthstown_IE">Edgeworth's Town</placeName><lb/></dateline>
               <salute>
                  My dear <persName ref="./Personography.xml#BeauF1">Francis</persName>, 
               </salute>
            </opener>
            <p>With compunction<lb/>
               on opening your letter I found three<lb/>
               pages devoted to my commissions -<lb/>
               Thank you - and to give you as little<lb/>
               further trouble I will answer shortly<lb/>
               and distinctly<lb/>
               <choice><orig>1<hi rend= "superscript">st</hi></orig><reg>Firstly</reg></choice> <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeR1">My father</persName> advises that I should<lb/>
               not buy the annual register at <hi rend= "underline"><choice><orig>pres</orig><reg>present</reg></choice> and</hi><lb/>
               <choice><orig>2<hi rend= "superscript">ly</hi></orig><reg>Secondly</reg></choice> I should like to have <title ref="./Workography.xml#Dicti1">Dic<hi rend= "superscript">y</hi> de l'Acad</title><lb/>
               - last Edit 1814 hand-bound <hi rend= "underline">good and</hi><lb/>
               <hi rend= "underline">almost</hi> new at <unclear>24<hi rend= "superscript">s</hi> 1/2 or 58 th<hi rend= "superscript">s</hi></unclear><lb/>
               <choice><orig>3<hi rend= "superscript">ly</hi></orig><reg>Thirdly</reg></choice> I should like to have M<hi rend= "superscript">rs</hi>. <persName ref="./Personography.xml#InchE1">Inchbald</persName>s<lb/>
               plays &amp; the farces In all the 53 <choice><orig>vol<hi rend= "superscript">s</hi></orig><reg>volumes</reg></choice><lb/>
               unbound - because we pay an <choice><orig>enor<lb/>
                  -mous</orig><reg>enormous</reg></choice> price <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeR1">my father</persName> says for bring<lb/>
               -ing over <hi rend= "underline">bound</hi> books<lb/></p>
               <p>In looking over the list of M<hi rend= "superscript">rs</hi>. <persName ref="./Personography.xml#InchE1">Inchbalds</persName><lb/>

               <pb n="2" facs="Edgeworth_Huntington_XXXX_1817_05_02_page02.jpg"/>
               
               collection of plays formerly, I could not<lb/>
               find the school for scandal or the rivals<lb/>
               but I suppose I overlooked them, I<lb/>
               can hardly imagine they can be omitted<lb/>
               If there should be any plays of merit<lb/>
               omitted or published since M<hi rend= "superscript">rs</hi>. <persName ref="./Personography.xml#InchE1">Inchbald</persName><lb/>
               made up her collection will you be<lb/>
               so kind to add them for me to that<lb/>
               collection - <lb/>
               Thank you for thinking of <title ref="./Workography.xml#WatTy1"><choice><orig>Watt</orig><reg>Wat</reg></choice> Tyler</title> &amp;<lb/>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#Sout1">Southey</persName>s pamphlett. <persName ref="./Personography.xml#MurrX1">M<hi rend= "superscript">r</hi>. Murray</persName> with<lb/>
               persevering civility has sent them<lb/>
               to me - But <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeC1">Sneyd</persName> lost <title ref="./Workography.xml#WatTy1">Wat Tyler</title> in<lb/>
               <placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#Dublin_IE">Dublin</placeName> &amp; the pamphlet is no sense<lb/>
               to us without it - therefore I should be<lb/>
               obliged by your sending it through <persName ref="./Personography.xml#MxxxE1">Sir E M</persName><lb/></p>
               <p>-	Your concluding <hi rend= "underline">ray of hope</hi> was<lb/>
               communicated only to <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeR1">my father</persName> &amp;<lb/>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeF2">M<hi rend= "superscript">rs</hi>. E</persName> - It delights them - <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeR1">my father</persName> <choice><orig>de-<lb/>
                  sires</orig><reg>desires</reg></choice> that I will <hi rend= "underline">only</hi> say that He knows<lb/>
               how to suppress curiosity even where he<lb/>
               is most interested -<lb/></p>
               <closer>
               Your sincerely affectionate<lb/>
               friend<lb/>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeM1">Maria Edgeworth</persName><lb/>
               </closer>

            <pb n="3" facs="Edgeworth_Huntington_XXXX_1817_05_02_page03.jpg"/>
            
               <postscript>
                  <p>I leave <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeF2">M<hi rend= "superscript">rs</hi>. E</persName> to give you an account of<lb/>
                  <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeR1">my father</persName> because I can more safely<lb/>
               trust her imagination &amp; judgment<lb/>
               than my own upon this as upon all<lb/>
               subjects -<lb/></p>
               <p>My dear <persName ref="./Personography.xml#BeauF1">Brother</persName><lb/></p>
               <p>I can say nothing favourable<lb/>
                  <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeR1">M<hi rend= "superscript">r</hi>. E</persName> has more fever - and less sickness<lb/>
               pulse at a 100 this morning - he is always<lb/>
               busy - but you may easily perceive<lb/>
               fever in his manner -<lb/>
                  Adieu <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeM1">M E</persName><lb/>
               I thank God for your ray of hope -</p><lb/>
               </postscript>

            <pb n="4" facs="Edgeworth_Huntington_XXXX_1817_05_02_page04.jpg"/>
            
<closer>
               <persName ref="./Personography.xml#EdgeM1">M. E.</persName><lb/>
               2 May 1817<lb/>
               
               MY 6<lb/>

            <address>
               <addrLine><persName ref="./Personography.xml#BeauF1">Capt<hi rend= "superscript">n</hi> Beaufort</persName></addrLine>
               <addrLine>R N</addrLine>
               <addrLine><placeName ref="./Placeography.xml#31-Harley-Street_ENK">31 Harley Street</placeName></addrLine>
            </address>

            <del></del><lb/>
            <del></del><lb/>
            <del></del><lb/>
